subject: wayland/X11: conditional build for wayland and X11
commitMessage:
wayland/X11: conditional build for wayland and X11

This patch turns the conditional the support to wayland or X11.
The wayland bits are not implemented, we're supposed to do so when
the other stuffs are ready - like window manager support and so on.

Change-Id: I329de3be59539848de6f8dbe3fc3a66de9c4b3da
Signed-off-by: Leandro Dorileo <leandro.maciel.dorileo@intel.com>

comments.message: Uploaded patch set 1.

Patch Set 1: Verified-1

(2 comments)

Generally speaking, I agree with this arch to align the util things together here, but it should not bring another stone to block the way.

is there any further patch to enable this package?

message-app depends on this package,  but this package is failed to build due to missing depends
=== the following packages failed to build due to missing build dependencies (1) ===
capi-ui-efl-util:
  nothing provides pkgconfig(x11)
  nothing provides pkgconfig(utilX)

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Generally speaking, I agree with this arch to align the util things together here, but it should not bring another stone to block the way.

is there any further patch to enable this package?

message-app depends on this package,  but this package is failed to build due to missing depends
=== the following packages failed to build due to missing build dependencies (1) ===
capi-ui-efl-util:
  nothing provides pkgconfig(x11)
  nothing provides pkgconfig(utilX)


But the code looks good to me, it's a good beginning to fix this package.

Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

One more thing to fix: should conditionally introduce X11 and utilX in spec file.

Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

Patch Set 1:

I tried to build this package against wayland repo which has no ecore-x and X related packages. Before build, I remove "BuildRequires(x11) BuildRequires(utilX)" in spec file to avoid dependency check failure. But I got the following error report:

[   64s] /usr/src/packages/BUILD/capi-ui-efl-util-0.1.0/src/efl_util.c:27:18: error: #if with no expression
[   64s]  #if ECORE_X_FOUND
[   64s]                   ^   

I think it is caused by "#define ECORE_X_FOUND @ECORE_X_FOUND@" in config.h.in. When build against wayland case, ecore-x will not be found, so that @ECORE_X_FOUND@ will be blank and hence ECORE_X_FOUND be blank.
Patch Set 1: -Verified Code-Review+2

Patch Set 1: Verified+1

https://review.tizen.org/gerrit/#/c/16328/ fixed the build issue
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.
